CTY1S.HE.summary: Citycon Oyj, a real estate investment company, owns, develops, and manages retail, office space, and housing properties in the Nordic region. The company owns 40 centers and 1 other retail property. Citycon Oyj was founded in 1988 and is headquartered in Espoo, Finland.

KOJAMO.HE.summary: Kojamo Oyj, a private residential real estate company, provides rental apartments and housing services in Finland. The company rents and manages apartments under the Lumo brand name. As of December 31, 2019, it operated 35,272 rental apartments. The company was formerly known as VVO Group plc and changed its name to Kojamo Oyj in March 2017. Kojamo Oyj was founded in 1969 and is headquartered in Helsinki, Finland.

L7G.F.summary: Lehto Group Oyj, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the construction and real estate business in Finland. It constructs business, housing, and social care and educational premises. Lehto Group Oyj was founded in 1976 and is headquartered in Kempele, Finland.
